{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Public `routerCallNative` lets callers execute arbitrary token `transferFrom` calls through the proxy and steal approved funds","locations":["Contract.sol:96","Contract.sol:117","Contract.sol:118","Contract.sol:129","FlawVerifier.sol:131","FlawVerifier.sol:147","FlawVerifier.sol:153","FlawVerifier.sol:165","FlawVerifier.sol:171"],"claim":"Both proxy variants expose `routerCallNative` with a caller-supplied `_params.router` target and caller-supplied raw `_data`. The reproduced exploit sets `router` to the USDC contract and encodes `_data` as `transferFrom(victim, attacker, amount)`, so the proxy itself performs the token call as the already-approved spender and transfers funds out of victims that previously approved the proxy.","impact":"Any user who has granted ERC20 allowance to either Rubic proxy can be permissionlessly drained up to the lesser of their balance and allowance. This is direct theft of user funds from existing approvals and is critical protocol-level loss.","paths":["Choose a victim that already approved one of the proxy contracts","Set `_params.router` to the approved ERC20 token contract","Encode `_data` as `transferFrom(victim, attacker, amount)`","Call `routerCallNative(...)` so the proxy executes the token call as spender and transfers the victim's tokens to the attacker"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Integrator identity appears spoofable, allowing public callers to inherit privileged routing permissions","source_agents":["codex"],"reason":"The reproduction hard-codes one `integrator` value, but the available code does not show that `integrator` is authenticated, permission-gating, or even consulted by the vulnerable path. The demonstrated theft is fully explained by arbitrary router target plus arbitrary calldata forwarding, so integrator spoofing is not independently supported."},{"title":"Declared swap/bridge parameters are not enforced against actual token movement","source_agents":["codex"],"reason":"The evidence only shows that these fields can be nonsensical while the arbitrary external call still succeeds. That is a symptom of the core arbitrary-call bug, not a distinct root cause with separate incremental impact, so it is merged into F-001 rather than kept as a separate finding."}]}
